verses.text_plain: Then Joseph could not refrain himself before all them that stood by him; and he cried, Cause every man to go out from me. And there stood no man with him, while Joseph made himself known unto his brethren.
verses.verse_html: 1Then Joseph could not refrain himself before all them that stood by him; and he cried, Cause every man to go out from me. And there stood no man with him, while Joseph made himself known unto his brethren.

tokens.text: himself before all them that stood

verses.text_plain: And he wept aloud: and the Egyptians and the house of Pharaoh heard.
verses.verse_html:
2And he wept aloud: and the Egyptians and the house of Pharaoh heard. ▼
▼ wept…: Heb. gave forth his voice in weeping

footnotes.body_text: ▼ wept…: Heb. gave forth his voice in weeping
footnotes.body_html: ▼ wept…: Heb. gave forth his voice in weeping

verses.text_plain: And Joseph said unto his brethren, I am Joseph; doth my father yet live? And his brethren could not answer him; for they were troubled at his presence.
verses.verse_html:
3And Joseph said unto his brethren, I am Joseph; doth my father yet live? And his brethren could not answer him; for they were troubled at his presence. ▼
▼ troubled: or, terrified

verses.text_plain: And Joseph said unto his brethren, Come near to me, I pray you. And they came near. And he said, I am Joseph your brother, whom ye sold into Egypt.
verses.verse_html: 4And Joseph said unto his brethren, Come near to me, I pray you. And they came near. And he said, I am Joseph your brother, whom ye sold into Egypt.

tokens.text: to me, I pray you. And they came near

verses.text_plain: Now therefore be not grieved, nor angry with yourselves, that ye sold me hither: for God did send me before you to preserve life.
verses.verse_html:
5Now therefore be not grieved, nor angry with yourselves, that ye sold me hither: for God did send me before you to preserve life. ▼
▼ nor…: Heb. neither let there be anger in your eyes

footnotes.body_text: ▼ nor…: Heb. neither let there be anger in your eyes
footnotes.body_html: ▼ nor…: Heb. neither let there be anger in your eyes

verses.text_plain: For these two years hath the famine been in the land: and yet there are five years, in the which there shall neither be earing nor harvest.
verses.verse_html: 6For these two years hath the famine been in the land: and yet there are five years, in the which there shall neither be earing nor harvest.

verses.text_plain: And God sent me before you to preserve you a posterity in the earth, and to save your lives by a great deliverance.
verses.verse_html:
7And God sent me before you to preserve you a posterity in the earth, and to save your lives by a great deliverance. ▼
▼ to preserve…: Heb. to put for you a remnant

footnotes.body_text: ▼ to preserve…: Heb. to put for you a remnant
footnotes.body_html: ▼ to preserve…: Heb. to put for you a remnant

verses.text_plain: So now it was not you that sent me hither, but God: and he hath made me a father to Pharaoh, and lord of all his house, and a ruler throughout all the land of Egypt.
verses.verse_html: 8So now it was not you that sent me hither, but God: and he hath made me a father to Pharaoh, and lord of all his house, and a ruler throughout all the land of Egypt.

verses.text_plain: Haste ye, and go up to my father, and say unto him, Thus saith thy son Joseph, God hath made me lord of all Egypt: come down unto me, tarry not:
verses.verse_html: 9Haste ye, and go up to my father, and say unto him, Thus saith thy son Joseph, God hath made me lord of all Egypt: come down unto me, tarry not:

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt dwell in the land of Goshen, and thou shalt be near unto me, thou, and thy children, and thy children’s children, and thy flocks, and thy herds, and all that thou hast:
verses.verse_html: 10And thou shalt dwell in the land of Goshen, and thou shalt be near unto me, thou, and thy children, and thy children’s children, and thy flocks, and thy herds, and all that thou hast:

tokens.text: unto me, thou, and thy children

verses.text_plain: And there will I nourish thee; for yet there are five years of famine; lest thou, and thy household, and all that thou hast, come to poverty.
verses.verse_html: 11And there will I nourish thee; for yet there are five years of famine; lest thou, and thy household, and all that thou hast, come to poverty.

tokens.text: and all that thou hast, come to poverty

verses.text_plain: And, behold, your eyes see, and the eyes of my brother Benjamin, that it is my mouth that speaketh unto you.
verses.verse_html: 12And, behold, your eyes see, and the eyes of my brother Benjamin, that it is my mouth that speaketh unto you.

verses.text_plain: And ye shall tell my father of all my glory in Egypt, and of all that ye have seen; and ye shall haste and bring down my father hither.
verses.verse_html: 13And ye shall tell my father of all my glory in Egypt, and of all that ye have seen; and ye shall haste and bring down my father hither.

tokens.text: and of all that ye have seen

verses.text_plain: And he fell upon his brother Benjamin’s neck, and wept; and Benjamin wept upon his neck.
verses.verse_html: 14And he fell upon his brother Benjamin’s neck, and wept; and Benjamin wept upon his neck.

verses.text_plain: Moreover he kissed all his brethren, and wept upon them: and after that his brethren talked with him.
verses.verse_html: 15Moreover he kissed all his brethren, and wept upon them: and after that his brethren talked with him.

verses.text_plain: And the fame thereof was heard in Pharaoh’s house, saying, Joseph’s brethren are come: and it pleased Pharaoh well, and his servants.
verses.verse_html:
16And the fame thereof was heard in Pharaoh’s house, saying, Joseph’s brethren are come: and it pleased Pharaoh well, and his servants. ▼
▼ pleased…: Heb. was good in the eyes of Pharaoh

footnotes.body_text: ▼ pleased…: Heb. was good in the eyes of Pharaoh
footnotes.body_html: ▼ pleased…: Heb. was good in the eyes of Pharaoh

verses.text_plain: And Pharaoh said unto Joseph, Say unto thy brethren, This do ye; lade your beasts, and go, get you unto the land of Canaan;
verses.verse_html: 17And Pharaoh said unto Joseph, Say unto thy brethren, This do ye; lade your beasts, and go, get you unto the land of Canaan;

verses.text_plain: And take your father and your households, and come unto me: and I will give you the good of the land of Egypt, and ye shall eat the fat of the land.
verses.verse_html: 18And take your father and your households, and come unto me: and I will give you the good of the land of Egypt, and ye shall eat the fat of the land.

tokens.text: unto me: and I will give

verses.text_plain: Now thou art commanded, this do ye; take you wagons out of the land of Egypt for your little ones, and for your wives, and bring your father, and come.
verses.verse_html: 19Now thou art commanded, this do ye; take you wagons out of the land of Egypt for your little ones, and for your wives, and bring your father, and come.

verses.text_plain: Also regard not your stuff; for the good of all the land of Egypt is yours.
verses.verse_html:
20Also regard not your stuff; for the good of all the land of Egypt is yours. ▼
▼ regard…: Heb. let not your eye spare, etc.

footnotes.body_text: ▼ regard…: Heb. let not your eye spare, etc.
footnotes.body_html: ▼ regard…: Heb. let not your eye spare, etc.

verses.text_plain: And the children of Israel did so: and Joseph gave them wagons, according to the commandment of Pharaoh, and gave them provision for the way.
verses.verse_html:
21And the children of Israel did so: and Joseph gave them wagons, according to the commandment of Pharaoh, and gave them provision for the way. ▼
▼ commandment: Heb. mouth

verses.text_plain: To all of them he gave each man changes of raiment; but to Benjamin he gave three hundred pieces of silver, and five changes of raiment.
verses.verse_html: 22To all of them he gave each man changes of raiment; but to Benjamin he gave three hundred pieces of silver, and five changes of raiment.

tokens.text: To all of them he gave

verses.text_plain: And to his father he sent after this manner; ten asses laden with the good things of Egypt, and ten she asses laden with corn and bread and meat for his father by the way.
verses.verse_html:
23And to his father he sent after this manner; ten asses laden with the good things of Egypt, and ten she asses laden with corn and bread and meat for his father by the way. ▼
▼ laden…: Heb. carrying

verses.text_plain: So he sent his brethren away, and they departed: and he said unto them, See that ye fall not out by the way.
verses.verse_html: 24So he sent his brethren away, and they departed: and he said unto them, See that ye fall not out by the way.

tokens.text: unto them, See that ye fall not out

verses.text_plain: And they went up out of Egypt, and came into the land of Canaan unto Jacob their father,
verses.verse_html: 25And they went up out of Egypt, and came into the land of Canaan unto Jacob their father,

verses.text_plain: And told him, saying, Joseph is yet alive, and he is governor over all the land of Egypt. And Jacob’s heart fainted, for he believed them not.
verses.verse_html:
26And told him, saying, Joseph is yet alive, and he is governor over all the land of Egypt. And Jacob’s heart fainted, for he believed them not. ▼
▼ Jacob’s: Heb. his

verses.text_plain: And they told him all the words of Joseph, which he had said unto them: and when he saw the wagons which Joseph had sent to carry him, the spirit of Jacob their father revived:
verses.verse_html: 27And they told him all the words of Joseph, which he had said unto them: and when he saw the wagons which Joseph had sent to carry him, the spirit of Jacob their father revived:

tokens.text: unto them: and when he saw

verses.text_plain: And Israel said, It is enough; Joseph my son is yet alive: I will go and see him before I die.
verses.verse_html: 28And Israel said, It is enough; Joseph my son is yet alive: I will go and see him before I die.
